  "_comment_architecture": [
    "Battery SHIPPING event (battery placed on the market / dispatched to a buyer).",
    "Purpose of this example: show how the Digital Product Passport master data is",
    "attached to the GS1 Digital Link (DL) identifier via masterDataAvailableFor, so",
    "a DL resolver / EPCIS repository can serve the passport for the shipped item.",
    "",
    "The epcList and every masterDataAvailableFor.id are GS1 Digital Link URIs",
    "(https://id.gs1.org/01/<GTIN>/21/<serial>). masterDataAvailableFor binds the",
    "product master-data record (the 'product card') to that DL identifier; this is",
    "the data a resolver returns when the printed QR / DL on the battery is scanned.",
    "",
    "masterDataAvailableFor carries gs1: product master data plus the eubat:-prefixed",
    "PRODUCT-LEVEL attributes and the cross-cutting passport metadata (schema:schemaVersion,",
    "schema:status, oec:reportingGranularity, oec:lastUpdated) — identical to the",
    "commissioning event for this SKU. Extension properties stay at PRODUCT level here",
    "because they describe the GTIN, not this shipment. Shipment-specific facts",
    "(buyer, transaction) ride in destinationList / bizTransactionList at event level.",
    "",
    "HTTP header: GS1-Extensions: oec=https://ref.openepcis.io/extensions/common/core/,eubat=https://ref.openepcis.io/extensions/eu/battery/",
    "The header activates regulation-specific validation and the SAMM/GEFEG export.",
    "See: extensions/common/core/docs/EPCIS_MASTERDATA_AND_EXTENSIONS.md",
    "and extensions/eu/battery/docs/URL_PATTERNS.md (DL resolver routing)."
  ],
